# Theme (Panda)

- **Recipes**: Define in `src/theme/recipes/*.ts` with `defineRecipe` or
  `defineSlotRecipe`. Export from `src/theme/recipes/index.ts` and list in
  `panda.config.ts` under `theme.extend.recipes` / `slotRecipes`. Set **jsx** to
  the component names that use the recipe.
- **Tokens**: Add palette tokens in `src/theme/colors/*`. Define the semantic
  token contract in `src/theme/themes/contract.ts` and theme mappings in
  `src/theme/themes/*`. Components and recipes should rely on semantic roles
  such as `fg.default`, `fg.muted`, `fg.subtle`, `bg.default`, `border`,
  `accent.primary`, `accent.secondary`, `accent.tertiary`, `success`, `warning`,
  `error`, and `typing.*` instead of raw palette tokens. See
  `docs/design-system/theme-contract.md` for the full contract.
- **Conditions**: Extend in `src/theme/conditions.ts` (e.g. `_light`, `_dark`,
  `_hover`). Reference in theme with `_condition` or in recipes.
- **Colors**: Raw palette modules live in `src/theme/colors/*`. These palettes
  are mapped to semantic roles inside theme definitions (`src/theme/themes/*`).
  Components and recipes must not reference palette tokens directly.
- **Gradient tokens**: Each theme defines two gradient tokens.
  - `shader` — full-viewport ambient background; applied only via
    `ShaderBackground` at layout level. Uses alpha-channel palette tokens
    (`a1`–`a3`). Do not apply `bgGradient: "shader"` to individual components.
  - `marble` — compact theme-preview swatch; applied via the `ThemeMarble`
    component. Uses opaque palette scale steps (`9`).
  Raw CSS variable names (`var(--colors-mint-a3)`) are required inside gradient
  strings because Panda semantic tokens cannot be resolved in CSS gradient values.
  See `docs/design-system/shader-system.md` for the full shader system reference.
- After changing recipes, tokens, or conditions, run **`panda codegen`** (or
  `pnpm prepare`) so `styled-system` is updated.
